author: Mark Manson
description:
If you grew up with adults praising you for your intelligence, but now you’re stuck, watching life pass by while others pull ahead then this one's for you. In this video, I break down the uncomfortable psychology of why early intelligence often turns into adult paralysis, how your biggest strength quietly became your biggest weakness, and why protecting the identity of being “smart” is holding you back from real growth. This isn’t feel-good motivation or IQ worship, it’s a blunt look at failure, identity, and why learning to be bad at things might be the smartest move you ever make.
